{
  "name": "Psionics Mind Blank!",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Icons/Genjutsu.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You weave a guttural and visceral sound that echoes outward designed to create pockets of blank space in the minds of the listener. Select a creature whom can hear you within range. The target must make an Intelligence saving throw.</p><p>Critical Success: Affected creature is able to resist this Genjutsu's effects.</p><p>Success: Affected creatures next jutsu cast increases its cost by +4</p><p>Failure: Affected creature becomes unable to cast a jutsu they cast on their previous turn. If they would attempt to cast such a jutsu, it fails.</p><p>Critical Failure: Affected creature becomes unable to cast a jutsu they cast on their previous turn. If they would attempt to cast such a jutsu, it fails, and they suffer a splitting migraine taking 5d6 psychic damage.</p><p>For each rank you cast this jutsu above D-Rank, increase the cost of this jutsu by 3 and the number of creatures you can target by +1 and the damage by 1d6</p>",
